<div id="review_2210254300" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2210254300" />
    <a title="Osama Saadeh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/32947981-osama-saadeh"><img alt="Osama Saadeh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581014170p2/32947981.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2210254300?book_show_action=true">Jul 21, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Osama Saadeh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Osama Saadeh" href="/user/show/32947981-osama-saadeh">Osama Saadeh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2210254300" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer286661296270165171">This book is definitely appealing for the pragmatist realists since the author derives laws and maxims from reality. This way of thinking is antagonistic to the idealist thinking, but what is problematic with this book is that he‚Äôs presupposing the notion that laws derived from reality proven successful through ‚Äúexperience,‚Äù are somehow static. The ugly truth is it is not, reality is in constant change; what is considered a reality now, vastly differs from reality yesterday. This pragmatic way o</span>
  <span id="freeText286661296270165171" style="display:none">This book is definitely appealing for the pragmatist realists since the author derives laws and maxims from reality. This way of thinking is antagonistic to the idealist thinking, but what is problematic with this book is that he‚Äôs presupposing the notion that laws derived from reality proven successful through ‚Äúexperience,‚Äù are somehow static. The ugly truth is it is not, reality is in constant change; what is considered a reality now, vastly differs from reality yesterday. This pragmatic way of thinking is exhibited in various parts of the book, in which it conspicuously appears after this phrase: ‚Äúexperience shows us.‚Äù On the contrary, he exhibits extreme accuracy, portrayal, and analysis of the reality introduced in the book from the past. It seems as if it is the genesis of laws and Machiavelli is paving the way for it to be, and no doubt it is. The extraordinary notion to think about, is the reformism type of thinking that is so much consistent with pragmatism, in other words: leave people‚Äôs political concepts untouched, and we‚Äôll strive to change the consequences of their concepts, instead of uprooting their concepts that engender cruxes embodied in reality. In short, problems will perpetually continue, even when you try to remedy one; another will return which is very much in similitude with the ramifications of reformism. It is noteworthy to say, that the rudimentary idea of reformism, is solving the problem not the root cause of the problem, i.e. radicalism. At the latter, it is a good read to have some insight into the reality we live in now, and how this mainstream way of thinking dominates the politics of the world today.</span>
  <a data-text-id="286661296270165171" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


