<div id="review_2333497988" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2333497988" />
    <a title="Ajay Venkitaraman" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman"><img alt="Ajay Venkitaraman" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2333497988?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ajay Venkitaraman" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ajay Venkitaraman" href="/user/show/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman">Ajay Venkitaraman</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780226500362" href="/book/show/167924.Discourses_on_Livy">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=roman-history">roman-history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=politics">politics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/40535764-ajay-venkitaraman?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2333497988" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12902096034381611014">If The Prince is a concise read for the ways to be adopted by a prince, Discourses on Livy is an elaborate treatise about the way a republic should function, much of it is still relevant today. Reading this book took up my mindspace so much that I was hooked on accomplishing the reading and nothing else. If you love history, this is something you will definitely like, for the others, it becomes a bit difficult to sustain the liking. The language, fittingly seems medieval and that&apos;s another plus.</span>
  <span id="freeText12902096034381611014" style="display:none">If The Prince is a concise read for the ways to be adopted by a prince, Discourses on Livy is an elaborate treatise about the way a republic should function, much of it is still relevant today. Reading this book took up my mindspace so much that I was hooked on accomplishing the reading and nothing else. If you love history, this is something you will definitely like, for the others, it becomes a bit difficult to sustain the liking. The language, fittingly seems medieval and that's another plus. It has made me put a lot more books by Virgil, Homer, Plutarch and on Torquatus, Valerius, Hannibal, Scipio, etc on my to do list for the future, so if one has read some of these, then DL would offer a nice view of these. On the downside, for uninitiated readers, this can be a bit tedious, and for most people who are not very well versed with Roman history would find it difficult to make complete inter-chapter sense, hence necessitating multiple reads. <br /><br />PS: Awesome translation again by Harvey Mansfield and Nathan Tarcov, as they have done a great job at recreating the essence of Niccol√≤ Machiavelli's language.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12902096034381611014" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


