<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer18122097087778644581">Niccol√≤ di Bernardo dei Machiavelli was an Italian political philosopher, musician, poet, and playwright. He is a figure of the Italian Renaissance and a central figure of its political component, most widely known for his treatises on realist political theory (<i>The Prince</i>) on the one hand and republicanism (<i>Discourses on Livy</i>) on the other.</span>

</div>
</div>

